.TH TAGTEST ${MANNUM1_8} "March 3, 1995"
.SH NAME
tagtest \- \*(Fx tag line testing program
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ${SBIN}/tagtest
[
.I options
] input.tif
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I tagtest
is a program for testing the ``tag line'' support in the \*(Fx server.
.I tagtest
takes a
.SM TIFF/F
(\c
.SM TIFF
Class F) file and
generates a new
.SM TIFF/F
file that is a copy of the input file, but with sample tag lines imaged
across the top of each page.
Options are provided for specifying 
a tag line format string and a tag line font file.
If neither are specified, then
.I tagtest
will use builtin defaults.
.I tagtest
is designed for testing tag line format strings
and fonts before they are configured for use by the
facsimile server.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP 10
.BI \-f " file"
Image the tag line format string using the
Portable Compiled Font (\s-1PCF\s+1) in
.IR file .
By default
.I tagtest
looks for the font file
.BR fixed.pcf .
.TP
.BI \-m " format"
Use
.I format
when imaging tag lines.
If this option is not specified, then
.I tagtest
uses the format string ``From %%n|%c|Page %%p of %%t''.
.TP
.BI \-o " file"
Write output to
.IR file .
By default output is written to the file
.BR t.tif .
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IR faxsend (${MANNUM1_8}),
.IR hylafax-config (${MANNUM4_5})
